          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The differential cross section for the 2H(gamma,p)n",
                " reaction has been measured at several",
                " center-of-mass angles ranging from 50 to 143.degr.",
                " for proton energies between 0.8 and 1.8 GeV.",
                " The experiment was performed at SLAC-NPAS",
                " facility with the use of the 1.6 GeV/C",
                " spectrometer to detect the high energy protons",
                " produced by a bremsstrahlung beam directed at a",
                " liquid deuterium target. Contributions from",
                " concurrent disintegration by the residual electron",
                " beam were determined by measuring the proton yield",
                " without the Cu photon radiator. At angles not very",
                " far from 90 degree, the energy dependence of the",
                " cross sections is consistent with predictions of",
                " scaling using counting rules for consitituent",
                " quarks. At least one theoretical calculation based",
                " on a meson-baryon picture of the reaction is able",
                " to reproduce the magnitude and energy dependence",
                " of the 90 degree cross section. The angular",
                " distribution exhibits a large enhancement at",
                " backward angles at the higher energies."
              ]
            }
          ],
